case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Near complete or complete skeleton
case_circumstances: A fully-clothed human skeleton was found alongside a house, near a dryer vent, covered by blackberry bushes.  The individual was determined to be a white male, between 25-35 years of age at the time of death.  This individual had several skeletal anomalies such as defects of the spine (vertebrae) which may have or may not have caused symptoms in life.
